Package: argparse
Type: Package
Title: Command line argument parsing based on a string description of
        variables
Version: 1.0
Date: 2015-03-11
Author: Moritz Lell
Maintainer: Moritz Lell <moritz.lell@uni-potsdam.de>
Description: Parse an argument line using parseArguments(text). Text is
    something like this:
    "
     a | numeric   | <>    | Help text for a
     b | character | abc   | Help text for b
     c | logical   | FALSE | Help text for c
     d | numeric   | 1     | Help text for d"
    A list containing all command line arguments is returned, with defaults
    of optional arguments filled in as needed.
License: Public Domain.
Built: R 3.1.2; ; 2015-03-12 11:03:33 UTC; unix
